Supplementary Materials for ‘Final title to insert’

2022-09-24

Supplement S1: main analysis

Calculations

- Checking dataset formatting

view.errors.umbrella(dat, return = "messages")
## WARNING:
## - The confidence interval is not symmetric around the effect size (this is only a warning, not an error).

- Conduct main analyses

  • Between-study variance = Restricted maximum likelihood
  • Excess significance bias test = TESSPSST test
  • Small study effects test = Egger’s test
  • Within study correlation between outcomes = 0.8
umb <- umbrella(dat, method.var = "REML", method.esb = "TESSPSST", r = 0.8, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)

Stratification of the evidence

strat <- add.evidence(umb, criteria = "Ioannidis")

strat_pres = right_join(factor_data, summary(strat, het_max = TRUE, digits = 2)) %>%
  select(!Factor)
## Joining, by = "Factor"
## Adding missing grouping variables: `Factor`
DT::datatable(strat_pres, 
              rownames = FALSE, extensions = 'Buttons',
              options = list(  # options
                initComplete = DT::JS(
                  "function(settings, json) {",
                  "$(this.api().table().body()).css({'font-size': '60%'});",
                  "$(this.api().table().header()).css({'font-size': '60%'});",
                  "}"),
                scrollX = TRUE,
                dom = c('tB'),
                buttons = c('copy', 'csv', 'excel'),
                scrollY = "600px", 
                pageLength = 600,
                order = list(6, 'asc'),
                autoWidth = TRUE,

                  list(className = 'dt-center', 
                       targets = "_all"))))

Supplement S2: Sensitivy analyses

1. Removing >1000 criterion

Stratification of the evidence

strat.s1 <- add.evidence(umb, criteria = "Personalized",
                      class_I = c(p_value = 1e-6, esb_p = 0.05, egger_p = 0.05, I2 = 50, pi = "notnull"),
                      class_II = c(p_value = 1e-6, largest_CI = "notnull"),
                      class_III = c(p_value = 0.001),
                      class_IV = c(p_value = 0.05), verbose = FALSE)

strat_pres1 = right_join(factor_data, summary(strat.s1, het_max = TRUE, digits = 2)) %>%
